\":\"**Understanding class access modifiers**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the accessibility of package-private static synthetic classes. If it's package-private, then that's fine, but if it's private static, a different class in the same package still can't access it. I realize existing source helpers would encounter issues if the class is private. In Groovy 2, it seems like the synthetic class must be declared as package-private to work properly. It's an interesting puzzle to figure out!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering throwable in lambda**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to handle \\\"Throwable\\\" when resolving it in a lambda with `assertThrows`. It seems like `Executable.execute` is designed to throw a throwable, but I want to make sure I've got the final implementation right. I guess I need to clarify how to structure this best when working with lambdas in this context. It's a bit tricky, but I'm working through it!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added targeted coverage for `io.restassured.internal.RequestSpecificationImpl$_header_closure8`.\n\nFiles added:\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io/restassured/internal/RequestSpecificationImplHeaderClosure8Access.java`\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RequestSpecificationImplInner_header_closure8Test.java`\n\nWhat the test covers:\n- Invokes the Groovy compiler-generated `class$(String)` resolver for `_header_closure8`, reaching the `Class.forName(String)` dynamic-access site.\n- Verifies missing-class handling through the same resolver path.\n- Exercises the public `RequestSpecification.header(String, Object, Object...)` API to execute the header closure behavior with multiple header values.\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05b7fa2c47b2f08b016a00f9e905e881969180d51e79998973\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": 