[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Understanding class access modifiers**\n\nI'm thinking about the accessibility of package-private static synthetic classes. If it's package-private, then that's fine, but if it's private static, a different class in the same package still can't access it. I realize existing source helpers would encounter issues if the class is private. In Groovy 2, it seems like the synthetic class must be declared as package-private to work properly. It's an interesting puzzle to figure out!\n\n**Considering throwable in lambda**\n\nI'm thinking about how to handle \"Throwable\" when resolving it in a lambda with `assertThrows`. It seems like `Executable.execute` is designed to throw a throwable, but I want to make sure I've got the final implementation right. I guess I need to clarify how to structure this best when working with lambdas in this context. It's a bit tricky, but I'm working through it!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05b7fa2c47b2f08b016a00f9d9f6648196a6ab3fa6444a8a10\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAPnpyzgbZQQEKQdhZ0gHjsaabVs8zBiFOQKZ-hd-kOBUcw-aQnYBPMQrqwK_ea1n5rL0GWVi-JVg4VN4yVz5gPkXMciSA1C8d5rnL2zDLbN74WzbGdVUHHEk-AAUH33gox2T1t7AULeRjN7kyFpQ3FPAv6qBsJ223K-CD9mNvCXFED8wN-3s-04CMhgvQIt2EQbGa_lRr_J6zCZq6ISzw94UVPHJNHwaUCB0KZIhgT5kdD2z-gUNEx7l89j6ix9c7woqLVFM4tuDD570zDd2BDVNPeOdGb5kSUXVc-PzUJZ8thuLbe3m4TnXPsVm_GQoOn7-c1y6MDiW33RH2XUZMtFAEnGfFKUZgJwrsfthbzbnFNcN3ejBSFkN_sjjiQy4nCU0daB1fk23kcCt6hTjeBUA50np-GBzp0DrrokDLbPpa8aRJ5dpw5RITlKoe2UBoR4uRsNnOUGvfDwbYZyAhQvtAc2DVnwVk-1F_8QXrvIdusePc_vlJoObg8MiL4zc9IQ9FTfCgoyspigbdSKtNKnfg_eBh38OmpZfCS_t09oUjZ_4HuPvIy6yWEMs9Yw80hXA6YZwEqCHuSSmyXy-L-bIu9Y2CAs1oyQwWjCi4aFUR-w_DT3GjjnuGo-uD5oMJddgd4EUo6DUmpqHxisCZGJGg1tYsRA2t3ABSnOywu98u1RbGvcMwME7VjRMKXSnlpoJy82_T43BuOGK8MzqL49L1a_xQ71qxFOJvAO2e6kzWeJ2u1clOdVa_YJ-h1DJ1Jsb6Gc1uh3lwIO4-kED_iiE69g96Qv1_8wAAIBFE9DCA1HgvdSiz88KWDx4bwLnVw5TwIDETIssgR_H