 the method uses additional values. \\n\\nThe dynamic call site Class.forName isn't usually executed by the closure doCall; it appears only in the compiler-generated class$ method for type resolution. The header closure body references additionalHeaderValues and might depend on the Header class. If it’s not cached, the generated bytecode might call class$(\\\"io.restassured.http.Header\\\"). It seems the closure call site may invoke $get$$class$io$restassured$http$Header.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating class access and testing**\\n\\nThe report has revealed class$(String) itself rather than any specific calls inside doCall. It seems that the public API might access class$ for the Header class. Previously, the headerWithAdditionalValues likely executed but had no coverage — possibly because Groovy invoked class$ unexpectedly. \\n\\nI'm focusing on the active class now. Directly generated helpers should provide coverage. To ensure this, the test may need to utilize the generated helper without being swallowed by the Native Image. However, reports indicated no new coverage after the attempt, suggesting that tests might have run only under the JVM agent, leaving the source helper untracked in the build.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pVc8mlFSroTxgJ35B4Q0VcNv|fc_05b7fa2c47b2f08b016a00fa94fd5c8196bb7ae994cb1c1408", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RequestSpecificationImplInner_header_closure8Test.java", "limit": 180}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4593, "output": 709, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40630, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778449032125, "responseId": "resp_05b7fa2c47b2f08b016a00fa88d7fc8196b0b162492b4605ec"}}
