[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to figure out why `git diff` doesn't show the test file—is it because it's untracked? Maybe I need to use `git diff --no-index`. My concern is with `into(destinationDirectory)`, which expects a Provider<Directory>, and whether `copy` accepts that in Gradle. In `doLast`, the destinationDirectory property should be accessible for the compile task. I wonder if generated classes copied after compile will work flawlessly; if they’re up-to-date, `nativeTestCompile` may not run `compileTestJava`. There’s a clean workflow dilemma here.
